Their political party is different than I have.

22:24.476 --> 22:26.319
Their religion is different.

22:26.339 --> 22:31.526
And all these things, and that puts people in these, puts some labels on them.

22:31.847 --> 22:36.974
And if we don't watch out, we don't reach them for Christ because we've already labeled them.

22:38.216 --> 22:39.618
You're not just kind of what Jonah did.

22:39.938 --> 22:41.961
Well, those are the wicked Ninevites.

22:42.061 --> 22:42.802
I know them.

22:43.426 --> 22:49.235
I know what they've done, so I have no way going to show love to them.

22:51.779 --> 22:54.443
And we can't do that with other people that are around us.

22:54.543 --> 22:57.488
We have to say, Lord, help me see them the way you see them.

22:59.752 --> 23:02.516
Help me have a different perspective of that person.

23:04.900 --> 23:11.410
It's definitely clear that Jonah didn't think that they deserved

23:11.490 --> 23:12.351
repentance.

23:12.371 --> 23:14.493
They didn't deserve God's love.

23:14.854 --> 23:20.239
But that wasn't His place to come up with that idea, well, they don't deserve it.

23:22.542 --> 23:27.467
And we can look at people and think, well, they don't deserve to have God's forgiveness.

23:27.507 --> 23:29.469
My goodness, look what they did have done.

23:32.252 --> 23:41.362
But we need to realize here that the only antidote to finding my identity with Jesus is to know

23:42.210 --> 23:43.773
my worth to God.

23:44.073 --> 23:49.503
It's not found in any of the traits, the characteristics that I mentioned a moment ago.

23:49.543 --> 23:54.171
It's remembering God loved me enough one day.

23:54.191 --> 24:07.634
He loved me and pursued after me enough one day, drew me unto himself, that I came to know him as my personal Savior.

24:08.706 --> 24:17.335
we all should have that testimony of thanking God for the time that we were made aware that we were sinners and we needed Christ.

24:18.836 --> 24:20.758
And that's the thing with the world today.

24:21.799 --> 24:24.582
Jesus laid down His life for everyone.

24:26.724 --> 24:36.594
So when we understand that, when we understand that verse that we know so well of John 3, 16, for God so loved the world,

24:36.738 --> 24:42.225
that whosoever, those words, two words of world and whosoever are so important.

24:44.088 --> 24:53.781
I mean, the whole, all the words are important, but remembering those key words is a reminder to us that God loved the world.

24:54.742 --> 24:57.666
You know, Jesus had to get the disciples straight on that.

24:59.388 --> 25:03.093
They, they, they wasn't ready to take the word to the Gentiles.

25:04.635 --> 25:06.738
They, they had struggle with that for a while.

25:08.546 --> 25:17.539
And yet he finally got to them enough to realize, hey, hey, Paul, hey, Peter, these Gentiles need the gospel too.

25:19.843 --> 25:21.946
Thank goodness they came to the Gentiles.

25:24.089 --> 25:33.784
And as we recognize that every person who has lived on the face of this earth need to have an opportunity to trust Jesus.

25:36.568 --> 25:38.130
And so just like

25:38.210 --> 25:43.216
Then I can bring to the table here, hey, here's God.

25:44.478 --> 25:46.020
He sent His Son to die for you.

25:46.941 --> 25:48.342
Won't you accept Him today?

25:49.724 --> 25:52.047
So we have to remember that.

25:52.267 --> 25:55.311
And sometimes we just have to re-remind ourselves.

25:57.253 --> 26:03.100
Every day of our lives, we need to remind ourselves that God has done what He's done for us personally.

26:04.863 --> 26:07.666
You know, God did something for you and me yesterday, didn't He?

26:08.674 --> 26:11.658
We're here today because God did something for us yesterday.

26:11.739 --> 26:14.262
He brought us through that day safely.

26:15.905 --> 26:16.906
He watched over us.

26:16.986 --> 26:17.848
He protected us.

26:19.029 --> 26:20.091
He met our needs.

26:21.653 --> 26:31.788
And today he's going to do something else for a lot of people who know someone we're walking these doors today lost and he's ready to save him today.

26:33.531 --> 26:35.013
That's the wonderful thing about it.

26:35.153 --> 26:38.258
And we should remind ourselves that

26:38.402 --> 26:41.728
God's ready to do something great every day.

26:41.748 --> 26:52.365
I think we also need to be reminded that we aren't owed anything by God or by anyone else.

26:53.928 --> 26:56.633
You know, I see that so much in our society today.

26:56.773 --> 27:04.626
It's like there are so many people who grow up and you see them, you hear them on the news, you see what's going on and they feel like that

27:04.706 --> 27:08.412
Somebody owes them something all day long every day.

27:09.794 --> 27:10.615
You owe me this.

27:10.675 --> 27:11.536
You owe me this.

27:13.499 --> 27:18.106
But the thing is this, God doesn't owe us anything.

27:18.146 --> 27:20.730
He doesn't because of His love and mercy towards us.

27:23.875 --> 27:34.130
I'm convinced if we took this one step at the beginning of every day, we'd be a lot better positioned to love others the way that God has loved us.

27:36.066 --> 27:54.204
I think maybe we changed a lot of things that we say or do, because the more we reflect on what God's done for us personally, the more likely we're to continue to move on to the next step, and that's be a mercy giver, showing mercy to someone else.

27:56.206 --> 28:01.031
You know, when you think about Jonah, he had no problem receiving God's mercy.

28:03.193 --> 28:04.274
He had no problem.

28:04.642 --> 28:10.969
praying in the belly of the whale and then being spit out and then going and saying, you know what?

28:11.029 --> 28:12.811
God has shown me mercy.

28:14.653 --> 28:18.757
When the Lord came up, he said, Oh, this is nice, nice shady spot.

28:20.379 --> 28:25.865
He had no problem with those times where he received God's mercy and he liked that.

28:27.627 --> 28:30.930
But he had a problem extending that mercy to someone else.

28:33.250 --> 28:39.196
Jesus reminded his disciples the importance of passing that on to others.

28:41.538 --> 28:44.801
Let's look at Luke 6, 27 and 38 through 38.

28:45.141 --> 28:47.504
Now these are very hard verses to do.

28:49.686 --> 28:55.691
But I say unto you, which hear love your enemies and do good to them which hate you.

28:57.393 --> 29:02.738
Bless them that curse you, pray for them, which despitefully use you.

29:04.066 --> 29:07.950
And unto him that smiteeth thee on one cheek, all for the other.

29:09.411 --> 29:14.517
And him that takeeth the way thy cloak, forbid not to take thy coat also.

29:16.078 --> 29:23.286
Give to every man that askseth of thee, and of him that takeeth the way thy goods, ask them not again.

29:23.306 --> 29:31.474
And as you would, that men should do to you, do you also to them likewise.

29:32.994 --> 29:37.620
For if you love them which love you, what thank have ye.

29:38.280 --> 29:41.044
For sinners also love those that love them.

29:42.766 --> 29:47.652
And if you do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye.

29:48.112 --> 29:51.076
For sinners also do even the same.

29:52.878 --> 29:58.004
And if you lend to them of whom you hope to receive, what thank have ye.

29:58.685 --> 30:02.770
For sinners also lend to sinners and receive as much again.

30:04.194 --> 30:20.038
But love ye your enemies and do good and lend, hoping for nothing again, and your reward shall be great, and ye shall be the children of the highest, for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil."

30:21.059 --> 30:22.722
Jonah need to be reminded of that.

30:23.743 --> 30:29.913
Be therefore merciful as your father also is merciful.

30:29.933 --> 30:30.834
Judge not,

30:31.234 --> 30:35.339
and you shall not be judged, condemn not, and shall not be condemned.

30:35.359 --> 30:37.602
Forgive and you shall be forgiven.

30:39.004 --> 30:41.146
Give and it shall be given unto you.

30:41.186 --> 30:53.221
Good measure, press down, shaken together, running over shall men give unto your bosom for with the same measure that you meet with all that shall be measured to you again.

30:53.241 --> 30:55.724
Those verses are not easy, are they?

30:57.487 --> 31:00.210
But you see, in every one of those verses,

31:00.706 --> 31:06.412
It's actually saying, we're not looking for someone to do us good first.

31:08.254 --> 31:11.117
We're not looking for my enemy to love me first.

31:12.038 --> 31:18.304
I'm not looking for someone to forgive me first, but I'm gonna do that first to them.

31:18.364 --> 31:21.788
I'm gonna love my enemies.

31:22.548 --> 31:23.810
I'm gonna pray for them.

31:23.870 --> 31:28.114
I'm gonna give to them, not expecting anything in return.

31:28.226 --> 31:31.210
I'm going to do the right thing as a child of God.

31:31.992 --> 31:35.216
And what that does is it expresses God's love to them.

31:36.859 --> 31:46.273
You see, he referenced many times the center can do some of those things, but people don't see God's love.

31:47.314 --> 31:53.744
But when we do it out of the right heart and the right attitude, then things are going to change.

31:53.844 --> 31:55.346
Things are going to be turned around.

31:56.866 --> 32:07.578
It's easy for us to read the book of Jonah and sit back and criticize him for not wanting to extend God's mercy to these Ninevites.

32:09.320 --> 32:14.326
But we need to really be careful to make sure we're not doing the very exact same thing.

32:14.546 --> 32:17.169
We're not doing the same thing that Jonah was doing.

32:18.791 --> 32:21.394
And I talked about it before, God's mercy

32:21.858 --> 32:25.964
which is often given to us in the form of second and third chances.

32:26.384 --> 32:31.091
It's also someone else's first chance sometimes to experience God's mercy.

32:33.774 --> 32:42.506
So when I talk about what we should be doing for Christ, you know it's going to cause us to be uncomfortable sometimes.

32:42.806 --> 32:51.378
You think that was a comfortable thing for Jonah to walk into that city of those wicked inner, he didn't know if anyone turned around and kill him on the spot.

32:52.738 --> 32:54.240
He knew what God had asked him to do.

32:54.260 --> 32:57.285
And if God finally got him to do, get there.

32:59.689 --> 33:01.593
But it was an uncomfortable position.

33:01.653 --> 33:03.616
Jonah would have rather been anywhere else.

33:05.880 --> 33:11.409
And we will be put in uncomfortable positions in our Christian walk many times.

33:15.035 --> 33:17.138
There was an author, Mike,

33:17.250 --> 33:45.106
Mittenberg, who was author of the Contagious Church, he said, there's Christians are all for evangelism and outreach, reaching the loss of Christ until those people start taking my parking spot at church, sitting in my pew, bringing kids to church who don't know how to behave, bringing worship music that I can't relate to.

33:45.922 --> 33:51.628
Then our comfort becomes more important than the souls of those people.

33:51.648 --> 33:52.369
Think about that.

33:53.951 --> 33:54.631
My goodness.

33:56.073 --> 34:01.098
Someone comes in and sits in the pew that I always sit in every Sunday.

34:02.880 --> 34:05.824
Am I gonna say, what are you doing in my pew?

34:06.384 --> 34:07.345
That's my pew.

34:08.787 --> 34:09.367
No, it ain't.

34:10.368 --> 34:11.350
It's not your pew.

34:12.751 --> 34:15.474
It's a place where someone can sit and hear the gospel.

34:17.026 --> 34:21.852
And if they parked in the space that, we know we are people of habit, aren't we?

34:21.932 --> 34:28.861
We got places we park, things we do, and if someone disrupts that schedule, my goodness, we get all been out of shape.

34:31.144 --> 34:35.810
I say, as a child of God, get been out of shape once in a while.

34:37.232 --> 34:45.522
Remember this, that someone is sitting in your pew that prays the Lord there here at the church, and they're here to hear the gospel.

34:47.266 --> 34:55.995
We should never get to the place where we think that our routine is more important than what God is wanting to do in someone's life.

34:58.277 --> 34:59.878
Get uncomfortable sometimes.

35:02.281 --> 35:08.887
We want to see the lost save, but sometimes we rather they get saved somewhere else.

35:08.907 --> 35:10.429
Oh my goodness, help us Lord.

35:12.731 --> 35:15.794
It describes Jonah to a T really.

35:15.970 --> 35:23.220
He had got to this point, as long as God only asked him to go bring the word of the Lord to his own people.

35:24.502 --> 35:25.524
And he's fine with that.

35:26.946 --> 35:32.173
But when he pulled him out of that comfort zone, he said, you could dinner the weather was wicked and then the lights are in preach.

35:33.234 --> 35:33.976
He didn't like it.

35:36.079 --> 35:38.482
He knew many of the people he was speaking to.

35:40.064 --> 35:44.210
And he did not like talking to them about this message, but

35:44.834 --> 35:51.381
He saw them as enemies of Israel, and it took him out of the comfort zone.

35:52.503 --> 36:03.395
So you and I, we have to realize we live our life on a daily basis, and there are gonna be times when God's gonna call you and me to be an instrument of mercy to someone else.

36:04.737 --> 36:13.106
And that's gonna require you to get out of your comfort zone, what you normally do, and do what God's asked us to do.

36:14.946 --> 36:20.652
It's going to be we're going to have to look for those opportunities that God has for us.

36:23.014 --> 36:26.617
My comfort of showing God's love.

36:26.657 --> 36:27.779
What's more important here?

36:29.500 --> 36:31.542
It's showing people who God is.

36:32.743 --> 36:39.630
And I said at the beginning of our series, as we close this out, and I'll tell you, we'll find ourselves.

36:39.650 --> 36:43.634
We are a lot more like Jonah than we care to admit in many ways.

36:45.762 --> 36:53.374
Instead of asking us to go to Nineveh and preach a message just one time, I believe God's calling us to go to our Nineveh every day.

36:55.478 --> 36:56.339
It's all around us.

36:58.703 --> 37:03.090
And we live in a culture of people who have largely turned away from God.

37:04.532 --> 37:10.662
They're serving other things, possessions, power, reputation, all kinds of other things.

37:12.224 --> 37:13.266
And because of that,

37:13.378 --> 37:16.684
We find the marriages are failing, homes are falling apart.

37:18.267 --> 37:22.294
Things are happening to our civilization all around us.

37:22.374 --> 37:23.916
Just turn on the news every day.

37:26.461 --> 37:29.827
And we see these things all around us, none of us all around us.

37:33.153 --> 37:38.482
And it's whether we're going to step through that door and share God's love or not.

37:40.770 --> 37:42.653
every day we're faced with a decision.

37:42.673 --> 37:44.655
Well, I go to none of them, my none of them.

37:45.497 --> 37:55.370
Well, I love people that don't love me, that are different than me, or am I going to make it all about myself and my comfort.

37:58.395 --> 38:06.867
You know, I think many times the view of the church, we got it wrong sometimes.

38:06.887 --> 38:09.330
We think if we just come into a building,

38:09.666 --> 38:17.557
And we just worship and praise and hear some good preaching, do some good singing and go back out the door and wait for next Sunday.

38:17.577 --> 38:19.279
We've done what we supposed to do.

38:21.802 --> 38:29.853
But the truth of the matter is we're hoping to fill these pews every Sunday with people that need to hear the gospel.

38:29.873 --> 38:33.097
And when we leave out of these doors, we're going out into our Nineveh.

38:33.117 --> 38:34.800
We're going out into our mission field.

38:35.180 --> 38:39.506
We're going out with the gospel, with what we've heard, what we've experienced in here.

38:41.346 --> 38:43.489
And we're sharing that with people that need to hear it.

38:45.973 --> 38:53.305
I can only imagine the impact that we would have on this world if more of our people would do that.

38:53.325 --> 38:55.628
More of our churches worldwide would do that.

38:56.289 --> 39:01.377
And don't get me wrong, we got good churches, good groups of people that are reaching the world.

39:02.720 --> 39:06.866
I'm so thankful to see more and more new faces coming into our church here.

39:07.714 --> 39:11.278
coming in and people being baptized and saved.

39:11.398 --> 39:12.520
That's what it's all about.

39:16.084 --> 39:17.185
But time's running out.

39:18.086 --> 39:20.329
You remember the deadline he gave Jonah?

39:20.349 --> 39:25.936
He said, you only got this many days and it's going to be it.

39:25.956 --> 39:30.882
I don't know when Christ is going to return, but I can tell you by looking at things around it, it can't be much longer.

39:30.902 --> 39:31.563
It just can't be.

39:33.485 --> 39:36.529
So we have to be urgent about the message that we do have.

39:36.549 --> 39:37.650
And that's the share.

39:37.794 --> 39:43.540
God's love and mercy to those who don't deserve it.

39:43.560 --> 40:00.056
And that means sometimes just going home, inviting your neighbors, doing something for them, looking for opportunities wherever we're out and about, and reaching and talking to people, having conversations with people, and showing them what Christ is all about.

40:02.139 --> 40:05.522
So if we want to love others,

40:06.210 --> 40:07.252
like God loves me.

40:07.272 --> 40:11.558
And I think if I ask every one of us this morning, aren't you thankful that God loves you?

40:12.639 --> 40:14.843
We'd all say, yes, praise the Lord.

40:16.485 --> 40:22.474
We've all heard great testimonies how people just thank God for His love and mercy every day.

40:22.494 --> 40:29.705
And if I'm that thankful for it, and if I mean what I say, then I can't make it all about myself.

40:29.785 --> 40:34.732
I have to realize other people need to know God's love and mercy too.

40:34.752 --> 40:36.114
So we have to share that.

40:37.346 --> 40:40.550
You know, the book of Jonah's interesting how it ended.

40:44.215 --> 40:46.578
God's questioning there right at the very end.

40:47.720 --> 40:48.641
God's asking him.

40:50.003 --> 40:52.266
We don't see what else God said.

40:52.306 --> 40:53.748
We don't know what Jonah said.

40:56.272 --> 40:59.476
I think he kind of left it open for us to search our life.

41:00.477 --> 41:04.783
So hey, God may be asking us the same thing.

41:04.803 --> 41:07.026
So let's reach all none of them for Christ.

41:08.258 --> 41:10.040
Well, it's been a good study for me.

41:10.400 --> 41:12.102
I pray it has for you.

41:12.822 --> 41:14.704
I've enjoyed teaching on the book of Jonah.

41:15.105 --> 41:15.365
Amen.

41:17.927 --> 41:22.432
Come back and hear, brother Danny, next Sunday as he continues his lessons.

41:22.452 --> 41:24.234
I've been good, some good studies there.

41:24.294 --> 41:36.786
As far as when I'm going to be teaching on next to the Lord, I'm always open to listening to the Lord as I study and teach and I'm going to be teaching on prayer.

41:37.538 --> 41:38.819
How important is prayer?

41:39.980 --> 41:47.908
And what I did is I went back and this is what the thought that the Lord gave me that I went back and I've already started putting it together.

41:48.429 --> 41:55.176
We'll look at prayer, we'll look at what it is, what it means, those things and introduction part of it.

41:55.696 --> 42:03.063
But starting at the beginning of the Bible in different places as we go along through the Bible, this is what I came up with and what the Lord showed me.

42:03.624 --> 42:05.746
What happened when they prayed?

42:07.106 --> 42:08.688
What happened when they really prayed?

42:09.609 --> 42:15.778
There are instances it says, and they prayed, and then this happened.

42:15.798 --> 42:16.559
This took place.

42:18.561 --> 42:23.508
Prayers are a great, important thing we have in our life to be able to pray.

42:24.590 --> 42:32.560
And you'll see that some great things were accomplished in the Bible when they prayed, got down to business and prayed.

42:32.961 --> 42:34.603
And I think we need to do the same thing.

42:35.084 --> 42:36.786
We need to remember we have to pray.

42:38.114 --> 42:42.880
You want to see answers to things in your family and your life in your church, then pray.

42:44.021 --> 42:45.143
Pray and ask God for those.

42:45.323 --> 42:48.427
Don't just sit back and wait for it to happen.

42:48.447 --> 42:50.629
But pray and see what's going to take place.

42:51.010 --> 42:53.533
Amen.

42:53.553 --> 42:55.515
You listen to Pastor David Kogel.

